annotationA: Elongation factor 1-gamma; Ef1gamma associates with other EF1 subunits (alpha/beta/delta). It binds tubulin and Doa protein kinase, which in turns phosphorylates Ef1gamma. Ef1gamma regulates organelle movement along microtubules
annotationB: Burgundy, isoform B; GMP synthase activity; ATP binding; pyrophosphatase activity; deubiquitinase activator activity; GMP synthase (glutamine-hydrolyzing) activity. It is involved in the biological process described with: histone deubiquitination; regulation of ubiquitin-specific protease activity; axon guidance; GMP biosynthetic process
